<seg id=1> China To Speed Up Development Of Human Resources Market </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Beijing, Sept. 1: The Organization Department and the Human Affairs Department of the Communist Party of China Central Committee issued notice recently that they will promote the healthy growth of the human resources market by improving and hastening its development plan. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> They said that the overall goals for cultivating and developing the human resources market are: employees may, of their own will, select an industry to work in; companies may, of their own will, choose employees; the market will adjust to supply and demand; social services will be perfected; and social security will be improved. The macroscopic regulation and control of the country will make the market function as a foundation for allocating human resources. </seg>
<seg id=4> Immediate goals include: drafting, within the next two to three years, the necessary basic regulatory policy for the human resources market; setting up widespread human resources marketplaces in large and mid-sized cities; establishing and developing localized job information networks; supporting development of the professional human resources market; and establishing regional human resource markets. </seg>
<seg id=5> Before the year 2000 the first steps in setting up a nationwide human resources market system that is functionally and mechanically sound, has a complete set of laws and regulations, gives timely guidance, and provides attentive and satisfactory service, should be in place. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In order to gradually setup a perfect human resources market system, the Organization Department and the Human Affairs Department require that the human affairs department at each level of the organization strengthen the setup and administration of the human resources market, to improve research and planning, to establish the complete layout and implementation of its development, to take suitable measures for different locations, and to provide classified guides. </seg>
</p>
